HEADWORD: Crandall
<hw>Cran"dall</hw> <pr>(kr⟦acr⟧n"d⟦ait⟧l)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos>
<ety>[Prob. from <etsep>Crandall</etsep>, a proper name.]</ety>
<fld>(Stonecutting)</fld> <def>A kind of hammer having a head formed of
a group of pointed steel bars, used for dressing ashlar, etc.</def> --
<def2><pos>v. t.</pos> <def>To dress with a crandall.</def></def2>⟦br⟧
[<source>Webster 1913 Suppl.</source>]</p>

